If any route handler becomes async in the future, thrown errors won't be caught without explicit handling in Express 4.x.

**Fix:** Use a wrapper or upgrade to Express 5 (which handles async errors natively), or use a utility:
```js
const asyncHandler = (fn) => (req, res, next) =>
  Promise.resolve(fn(req, res, next)).catch(next);

app.get('/users', asyncHandler(async (req, res) => {
  // async logic — errors auto-forwarded to error handler
  res.json([...]);
}));
```

